<item>
            <title>[MNG-2130] Parent POM not created by reactor if not found in repository</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/MNG-2130</link>
                <project id="12316922" key="MNG">Maven (Moved to GitHub Issues)</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider a multi-module project with usual parent-child relationship&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;pom.xml&lt;br/&gt;
module-1/pom.xml&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
module-n/pom.xml&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Executing install goal from top-level fails due to failure to find parent POM in any repository&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Caused by: org.apache.maven.artifact.resolver.ArtifactNotFoundException: Unable to download the artifact from any repository&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &amp;lt;groupId&amp;gt;:&amp;lt;artifactId&amp;gt;:pom:&amp;lt;version&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using maven-2.0.2 this does not occur and the parent POM is installed if not found - as expected.&lt;br/&gt;
Hence a regression. &lt;/p&gt;
</description>
